NY.ADJ.AEDU.CD-ge.def: Education expenditure refers to the current operating expenditures in education, including wages and salaries and excluding capital investments in buildings and equipment.
NY.ADJ.AEDU.CD-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.AEDU.CD-ge.source: UNESCO; data are extrapolated to the most recent year available

NY.ADJ.AEDU.GN.ZS-ge.def: Education expenditure refers to the current operating expenditures in education, including wages and salaries and excluding capital investments in buildings and equipment.
NY.ADJ.AEDU.GN.ZS-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.AEDU.GN.ZS-ge.source: UNESCO; data are extrapolated to the most recent year available

NY.ADJ.DCO2.CD-ge.def: Cost of damage due to carbon dioxide emissions from fossil fuel use and the manufacture of cement, estimated to be US$40 per ton of CO2 (the unit damage in 2017 US dollars for CO2 emitted in 2020) times the number of tons of CO2 emitted.
NY.ADJ.DCO2.CD-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DCO2.CD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.DCO2.GN.ZS-ge.def: Cost of damage due to carbon dioxide emissions from fossil fuel use and the manufacture of cement, estimated to be US$40 per ton of CO2 (the unit damage in 2017 US dollars for CO2 emitted in 2020) times the number of tons of CO2 emitted.
NY.ADJ.DCO2.GN.ZS-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DCO2.GN.ZS-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.DFOR.CD-ge.def: Net forest depletion is calculated as the product of unit resource rents and the excess of roundwood harvest over natural growth. If growth exceeds harvest, this figure is zero.
NY.ADJ.DFOR.CD-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DFOR.CD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.DFOR.GN.ZS-ge.def: Net forest depletion is calculated as the product of unit resource rents and the excess of roundwood harvest over natural growth. If growth exceeds harvest, this figure is zero.
NY.ADJ.DFOR.GN.ZS-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DFOR.GN.ZS-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.DKAP.CD-ge.def: Consumption of fixed capital represents the replacement value of capital used up in the process of production.
NY.ADJ.DKAP.CD-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DKAP.CD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.DKAP.GN.ZS-ge.def: Consumption of fixed capital represents the replacement value of capital used up in the process of production.
NY.ADJ.DKAP.GN.ZS-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DKAP.GN.ZS-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.DMIN.CD-ge.def: Mineral depletion is the ratio of the value of the stock of mineral resources to the remaining reserve lifetime. It covers tin, gold, lead, zinc, iron, copper, nickel, silver, bauxite, and phosphate.
NY.ADJ.DMIN.CD-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DMIN.CD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.DMIN.GN.ZS-ge.def: Mineral depletion is the ratio of the value of the stock of mineral resources to the remaining reserve lifetime. It covers tin, gold, lead, zinc, iron, copper, nickel, silver, bauxite, and phosphate.
NY.ADJ.DMIN.GN.ZS-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DMIN.GN.ZS-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.DNGY.CD-ge.def: Energy depletion is the ratio of the value of the stock of energy resources to the remaining reserve lifetime. It covers coal, crude oil, and natural gas.
NY.ADJ.DNGY.CD-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DNGY.CD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.DNGY.GN.ZS-ge.def: Energy depletion is the ratio of the value of the stock of energy resources to the remaining reserve lifetime. It covers coal, crude oil, and natural gas.
NY.ADJ.DNGY.GN.ZS-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DNGY.GN.ZS-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.DPEM.CD-ge.def: Particulate emissions damage is the damage due to exposure of a country's population to ambient concentrations of particulates measuring less than 2.5 microns in diameter (PM2.5), ambient ozone pollution, and indoor concentrations of PM2.5 in households cooking with solid fuels. Damages are calculated as foregone labor income due to premature death. Estimates of health impacts from the Global Burden of Disease Study 2019. Data for other years have been extrapolated from trends in mortality rates.
NY.ADJ.DPEM.CD-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DPEM.CD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.DPEM.GN.ZS-ge.def: Particulate emissions damage is the damage due to exposure of a country's population to ambient concentrations of particulates measuring less than 2.5 microns in diameter (PM2.5), ambient ozone pollution, and indoor concentrations of PM2.5 in households cooking with solid fuels. Damages are calculated as foregone labor income due to premature death. Estimates of health impacts from the Global Burden of Disease Study 2019. Data for other years have been extrapolated from trends in mortality rates.
NY.ADJ.DPEM.GN.ZS-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DPEM.GN.ZS-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.DRES.GN.ZS-ge.def: Natural resource depletion is the sum of net forest depletion, energy depletion, and mineral depletion. Net forest depletion is unit resource rents times the excess of roundwood harvest over natural growth. Energy depletion is the ratio of the value of the stock of energy resources to the remaining reserve lifetime. It covers coal, crude oil, and natural gas. Mineral depletion is the ratio of the value of the stock of mineral resources to the remaining reserve lifetime. It covers tin, gold, lead, zinc, iron, copper, nickel, silver, bauxite, and phosphate.
NY.ADJ.DRES.GN.ZS-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.DRES.GN.ZS-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.ICTR.GN.ZS-ge.def: Gross savings are the difference between gross national income and public and private consumption, plus net current transfers.
NY.ADJ.ICTR.GN.ZS-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.ICTR.GN.ZS-ge.source: World Bank national accounts data files.

NY.ADJ.NNAT.CD-ge.def: Net national savings are equal to gross national savings less the value of consumption of fixed capital.
NY.ADJ.NNAT.CD-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.NNAT.CD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.NNAT.GN.ZS-ge.def: Net national savings are equal to gross national savings less the value of consumption of fixed capital.
NY.ADJ.NNAT.GN.ZS-ge.name: Adjusted savings
NY.ADJ.NNAT.GN.ZS-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.NNTY.CD-ge.def: Adjusted net national income is GNI minus consumption of fixed capital and natural resources depletion.
NY.ADJ.NNTY.CD-ge.name: Adjusted net national income
NY.ADJ.NNTY.CD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.NNTY.KD-ge.def: Adjusted net national income is GNI minus consumption of fixed capital and natural resources depletion.
NY.ADJ.NNTY.KD-ge.name: Adjusted net national income
NY.ADJ.NNTY.KD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.NNTY.KD.ZG-ge.def: Adjusted net national income is GNI minus consumption of fixed capital and natural resources depletion.
NY.ADJ.NNTY.KD.ZG-ge.name: Adjusted net national income
NY.ADJ.NNTY.KD.ZG-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.NNTY.PC.CD-ge.def: Adjusted net national income is GNI minus consumption of fixed capital and natural resources depletion.
NY.ADJ.NNTY.PC.CD-ge.name: Adjusted net national income per capita
NY.ADJ.NNTY.PC.CD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods in World Bank's "The Changing Wealth of Nations: Measuring Sustainable Development in the New Millennium" (2011).

NY.ADJ.NNTY.PC.KD-ge.def: Adjusted net national income is GNI minus consumption of fixed capital and natural resources depletion.
NY.ADJ.NNTY.PC.KD-ge.name: Adjusted net national income per capita
NY.ADJ.NNTY.PC.KD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods in World Bank's "The Changing Wealth of Nations: Measuring Sustainable Development in the New Millennium" (2011).

NY.ADJ.NNTY.PC.KD.ZG-ge.def: Adjusted net national income is GNI minus consumption of fixed capital and natural resources depletion.
NY.ADJ.NNTY.PC.KD.ZG-ge.name: Adjusted net national income per capita
NY.ADJ.NNTY.PC.KD.ZG-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods in World Bank's "The Changing Wealth of Nations: Measuring Sustainable Development in the New Millennium" (2011).

NY.ADJ.SVNG.CD-ge.def: Adjusted net savings are equal to net national savings plus education expenditure and minus energy depletion, mineral depletion, net forest depletion, and carbon dioxide and particulate emissions damage.
NY.ADJ.SVNG.CD-ge.name: Adjusted net savings
NY.ADJ.SVNG.CD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.SVNG.GN.ZS-ge.def: Adjusted net savings are equal to net national savings plus education expenditure and minus energy depletion, mineral depletion, net forest depletion, and carbon dioxide and particulate emissions damage.
NY.ADJ.SVNG.GN.ZS-ge.name: Adjusted net savings
NY.ADJ.SVNG.GN.ZS-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.SVNX.CD-ge.def: Adjusted net savings are equal to net national savings plus education expenditure and minus energy depletion, mineral depletion, net forest depletion, and carbon dioxide. This series excludes particulate emissions damage.
NY.ADJ.SVNX.CD-ge.name: Adjusted net savings
NY.ADJ.SVNX.CD-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.

NY.ADJ.SVNX.GN.ZS-ge.def: Adjusted net savings are equal to net national savings plus education expenditure and minus energy depletion, mineral depletion, net forest depletion, and carbon dioxide. This series excludes particulate emissions damage.
NY.ADJ.SVNX.GN.ZS-ge.name: Adjusted net savings
NY.ADJ.SVNX.GN.ZS-ge.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.
